	2020-09-16 bye bye, big tech

	hi, i think a lot about privacy on and offline. i want to get to
	a place where i no longer depend on products of mass consumption from
	FAANG (facebook,apple,amazon,netflix,google/alphabet). ive been slowly
	exporting my data from facebook, instagram, google, and fitbit and 
	backing it all up to prepare for when i actually "delete" my accounts. 
	unfortunately thats all i can do because a majority of these companies
	are known to store users data on their servers for years. the cloud
	scares me. the control i have over my own data almost makes me feel
	hopeless in the fight for privacy + security. but i wont let it stop
	me from doing everything i can to protect myself on the internet.
	right now, i am nowhere near reaching my goal and ive faced 
	several challenges in the process. my plan goes something like this...
	
	- google -> takeout data âˆš
       \
	 - gmail -> emails archived âˆš
	
	- fitbit -> takeout data âˆš
	
	- facebook -> takeout data âˆš
       \ 
	 - instagram -> takeout data
	
	- reddit -> takeout data âˆš

	- hypothesis -> takeout data âˆš    

	promnesia ~ * . *  .

